A group project team used a WhatsApp group to discuss a college assignment, but one member wasn't part of the group .
He missed crucial updates and submitted the wrong project, resulting in a poor grade for the team.
The team was frustrated, and their grade suffered due to this miscommunication.


What could've been done differently:
>Used a centralized platform like Google Drive or Trello for project updates
>Ensured all team members were included in key communications
>Confirmed receipt of important messages
>Set clear expectations for communication channels and response times


This situation highlights the importance of intentional digital communication, especially in group settings . 
Clear communication channels and protocols can prevent misunderstandings and save trouble .
